cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language inference (NLI) and evaluates the performance of state-of-the-art models on a new NLI test set. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) because it involves training and evaluating machine learning models. Additionally, it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) because NLI is a crucial task in natural language processing and computer vision applications.
